{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FxPPTtKS8dp4Lt7UbRsZgE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: uv crate — child.rs\n3\ttype: module\n4\tsources:\n5\t  - path: crates/uv/src/child.rs\n6\tgoals:\n7\t  - \"name 2 source files in uv crate\"\n8\tcreated: '2026-05-10'\n9\tupdated: '2026-05-10'\n10\trelated:\n11\t  - \"[[uv-lib]]\"\n12\tstale: false\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\t# uv crate — `child.rs`\n16\t\n17\t`crates/uv/src/child.rs` is a small focused module that owns one\n18\tresponsibility: waiting for a spawned child process to complete while\n19\tbehaving correctly under terminal signals (`SIGINT`, `SIGTERM`,\n20\t`Ctrl-C`).\n21\t\n22\tIt exposes a single `pub(crate)` async function:\n23\t\n24\t```rust\n25\t// from crates/uv/src/child.rs\n26\tpub(crate) async fn run_to_completion(mut handle: Child) -> anyhow::Result<ExitStatus> {\n27\t    // ...\n28\t}\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\t## Why it exists\n32\t\n33\tWhen `uv run` / `uv tool run` spawn a subprocess (a `tokio::process::Child`),\n34\tnaïvely awaiting its exit produces wrong behavior in interactive\n35\tterminals: the terminal driver sends `SIGINT` to the whole process\n36\tgroup on `Ctrl-C`, so the child would receive `SIGINT` once from the\n37\tdriver and a second time if `uv` forwarded its own copy. Some\n38\tprograms treat the second signal as \"fast exit\", so `uv` must\n39\tspecifically *not* forward `SIGINT` when the child is in the same\n40\tprocess group of an interactive TTY.\n41\t\n42\tThe module's docstring captures the reasoning in detail; the\n43\timplementation distinguishes Unix vs Windows and detects whether\n44\tstdin is a TTY to decide between *ignore* and *forward* policies.\n45\t\n46\t## Where it is called from\n47\t\n48\tIt is invoked by command handlers in `crates/uv/src/commands/` after\n49\tthey have configured a `tokio::process::Command` and called `spawn()`.\n50\tThe crate-level entry point is documented in [[uv-lib]].\n51\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e2c2964-0534-4426-96da-c0c93e819bb7","uuid":"0b535366-6714-4abe-9006-47fc463fcc79","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:13:04.615Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"D:\\side_project\\uv\\.codebus\\wiki\\modules\\uv-child.md","content":"---\ntitle: uv crate — child.rs\ntype: module\nsources:\n  - path: crates/uv/src/child.rs\ngoals:\n  - \"name 2 source files in uv crate\"\ncreated: '2026-05-10'\nupdated: '2026-05-10'\nrelated:\n  - \"[[uv-lib]]\"\nstale: false\n---\n\n# uv crate — `child.rs`\n\n`crates/uv/src/child.rs` is a small focused module that owns one\nresponsibility: waiting for a spawned child process to complete while\nbehaving correctly under terminal signals (`SIGINT`, `SIGTERM`,\n`Ctrl-C`).\n\nIt exposes a single `pub(crate)` async function:\n\n```rust\n// from crates/uv/src/child.rs\npub(crate) async fn run_to_completion(mut handle: Child) -> anyhow::Result<ExitStatus> {\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n## Why it exists\n\nWhen `uv run` / `uv tool run` spawn a subprocess (a `tokio::process::Child`),\nnaïvely awaiting its exit produces wrong behavior in interactive\nterminals: the terminal driver sends `SIGINT` to the whole process\ngroup on `Ctrl-C`, so the child would receive `SIGINT` once from the\ndriver and a second time if `uv` forwarded its own copy. Some\nprograms treat the second signal as \"fast exit\", so `uv` must\nspecifically *not* forward `SIGINT` when the child is in the same\nprocess group of an interactive TTY.\n\nThe module's docstring captures the reasoning in detail; the\nimplementation distinguishes Unix vs Windows and detects whether\nstdin is a TTY to decide between *ignore* and *forward* policies.\n\n## Where it is called from\n\nIt is invoked by command handlers in `crates/uv/src/commands/` after\nthey have configured a `tokio::process::Command` and called `spawn()`.\nThe crate-level entry point is documented in [[uv-lib]].\n","numLines":51,"startLine":1,"totalLines":51}}}
